Lambda Calculus Research Repository - License Information
============================================================

Copyright (C) 2025 Lambda Research Collective

This repository contains multiple types of content with different licensing:

1. SYNTHESIZED RESEARCH CONTENT (GPL-3.0)
==========================================
All original content created for this repository, including:
- Implementation code (Scala, Scheme, SML, Idris)
- Python scripts and automation tools
- Shell scripts
- Documentation and tutorials (Markdown files)
- Repository structure and organization
- Makefile and build systems

These are licensed under the GNU General Public License v3.0 (GPL-3.0).
See the LICENSE file for the full text.

How to apply GPL-3.0 to your contributions:
- Add copyright notice and GPL header to source files
- See existing files for examples
- Full license text in LICENSE file

2. LIBRARY COMPONENTS (LGPL-3.0)
=================================
Certain reusable library components that may be linked by other software:
- Reusable lambda calculus implementation libraries
- Standalone utility modules designed for linking

These are licensed under the GNU Lesser General Public License v3.0 (LGPL-3.0).
See the LICENSE.LGPL file for the full text.

3. ACADEMIC PAPERS AND EXTERNAL CONTENT (Various)
==================================================
PDF files and academic papers retain their original copyrights:
- Papers in docs/ and papers-archive/ directories
- External citations and bibliographies
- These are NOT relicensed and remain under their original terms
- Included under fair use for research and educational purposes
- See individual papers for their specific copyright information

4. THIRD-PARTY CONTENT
======================
Any third-party libraries or tools maintain their original licenses.
See individual files or directories for specific attribution.

USAGE GUIDELINES
================
- When using synthesized research code: Follow GPL-3.0 terms
- When linking library components: Follow LGPL-3.0 terms
- When citing papers: Respect original academic copyrights
- When contributing: Agree to license under GPL-3.0/LGPL-3.0

For more information:
- GPL-3.0: https://www.gnu.org/licenses/gpl-3.0.html
- LGPL-3.0: https://www.gnu.org/licenses/lgpl-3.0.html
- Questions: See README.md for contact information

This repository aims to advance lambda calculus research and education
while respecting both academic freedom and open source principles.
